{
  "answer": "**The poem is \"Tanhai\" (Solitude), Chapter 25 of *Bang-E-Dara Part 2* by Allama Iqbal.**[^1]\n\nThis work directly addresses a solitary heart (explicitly \"O heart!\" in the final stanza), telling it that the stars of the night sky are its companions (\"Are the stars sorrowful in the night? / Are they not your companions!\") and that Nature is its kindred spirit (\"For Nature is your kindred spirit, O heart!\"). The specified tear-into-star couplet appears in the fourth stanza:\n\n> These lovely pearls, so bright they are,  \n> Are but your tears, become a star.[^2]\n\n[^1]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 2*, Chapter 25 \"Tanhai,\" [translation](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-2-9bc58c/25-tanhai/translation/).\n[^2]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 2*, Chapter 25 \"Tanhai,\" [paragraph](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-2-9bc58c/25-tanhai/translation/#p-36f218).",
